<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      metal:use-macro="context/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="hive.lab"
      xml:lang="en"
      lang="en">
  <metal:content-core fill-slot="content-core">
    <metal:content-core define-macro="content-core">
        <tal:data define="form view/filter">
            <tal:hasdata tal:condition="form">
                <p>
                Enter the criteria you would like to use as a filter. The filter will persist while you are logged in. Be sure to remove the filter to make sure you are seeing all available aliquot if that is your wish.
                </p>
                <tal:crud replace="structure form" />
            </tal:hasdata>
        </tal:data>
        <br class="visualClear" />    
        <tal:data define="form view/crudform">
            <tal:hasdata tal:condition="form">
                <p><b>Note:</b> a filter is automatically applied depending on your location in the site; For isntance, if you view a patient's aliquot, it will filter by that patient. View all of a type of aliquot, and it will filter to show just that type.
                </p>
                <tal:crud replace="structure form" />
                <br class="visualClear" />
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <b>Queue & Hold</b>: Add the selected Aliquot to the checkout queue. The queue is available at the bottom of this screen.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                     <b>Mark Inaccurate</b>: Mark the selected aliquot as inaccurate. Edit them on the <a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/lab_url}/edit-aliquot">edit aliquot screen</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                     <b>Hold</b>: Place a hold on the aliquot. That will hide it in this view, and only make it available if the "Show all" option is selected in the filter above.
                    </li>
                    </ul>
            </tal:hasdata>
            <tal:nodata tal:condition="not:form">
                <p>
                No Aliquot match your filter, or there are no aliquot available in this context.
                </p>
            </tal:nodata>
        </tal:data>
        <hr class="visualClear" />

        <tal:data define="form view/aliquotqueue">
            <tal:hasdata tal:condition="form">
                <p>
                   Aliquot currently queued for checkout. After developing your queue, verify that the aliquot you want are available before removing them from this screen.
                </p>
                <tal:crud replace="structure form" />
                <br class="visualClear" />
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <b>Print List</b>: Print a list to take to storage.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b><a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/lab_url}/checkout">Check Out</a></b>: Place the selected aliquot in the fnial stage for check out. After you have selected all of the aliquot for check out, proceed to the <a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/lab_url}/checkout">check out screen</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b>Release from Queue</b>:Release the hold on the selected aliquot, returning them to a checked in state.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                     <b><a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/lab_url}/edit-aliquot">Mark Inaccurate</a></b>: Mark the selected aliquot as inaccurate. Edit them on the <a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/lab_url}/edit-aliquot">edit aliquot screen</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b>Mark Missing</b>: Mark the selected aliquot as missing.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </tal:hasdata>
            <tal:nodata tal:condition="not:form">
                <p>
                No aliquot in the checkout queue. 
                </p>
                <ul><li>Head to the <a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/lab_url}/checkout">Checkout</a> Screen to finalize the checkout process.</li>
                <li>Head to the <a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/lab_url}/edit-aliquot">Edit</a> Screen to modify incorrect aliquot.</li>
                </ul>
                </tal:nodata>
        </tal:data>
    </metal:content-core>
  </metal:content-core>
</html>